mes. They\nare recognized know-how. and\nthey know best.\nAs for the public having lots\nof money, the Securities and\nExchange Commission reports\nindividual actual \u201cliquid sav\nings\" for the first quarter at\n$4.8 billion. That'S S6OO mil\nlion less than the 1956 final\nquarter. And a recent survey\nby Michigan University's Re\nsearch Center of Consumer;\nPlanned Buying finds consumer\nconfidence weakening and a\ncut in planned buying.\nThe magazine Steel surveyed\nmost of the Nation's big mnnu- 1\nfacturers and found very little\nhope expressed for Increasing\nnet earnings over last year.\n1 Randolph Burgess. Undersecre\ntary of the Treasury. Is on rec\no\u00dfd saying; \u201cI suspect some\npeople are overoptimistlc about\ntheir markets.\u201d\nBanks are dubious about an\nupturn, too. The Guaranty\nj Trust of New York says; \"There\njis still no buoyancy in business\noperations. The expectation of\nan upturn is, in some measure,\nthe product of hope rather than\nof tangible signs.\" And the First\nNational City Bank of New\nYork says: \"The resumption of\ninventory growth in the sec\nond quarter may be involuntary\n\u2014backing up of finished goods\nin the hands of producers.\u201d\nI iCongolidatfrl Nr\u00ab, Praturni\nVISIBLC GRAIN\nli in\nL CHICAGO Aut 13 OTV\u2014The United\n1 State* visible supply of wheat Increased\n4.517.000 bushel* last wrek to 350.-\n130.000 bushel*, the Board of Trade\nsaid yesterday Corn decreased *L-\nI MH.f'OO bushel* to 11\\\\:19 t.ooo bushels:\nI oata Increased |.4\u2018J3.000 to 15/^O\u2018Loon.\nrye increased M'.\u2019.ooo to d.:mo,ooo\n.barley Increased 577,000 to *!H.777.000.\nand soybeans decreased 07,000 to\nft.A30.000,\nCUSTOM HOME BUILDERS\n50 Miles D. C. by\nR. H. BEST, -nc\nGet the best for less\nFREE Estimate While You Wait\n(15 Mins.) on any plan\nBuild the Best Built Woy tor\nAs low ot $lO per sq. ft.\nSee Onr Oisplay Homes\nat\n1545 Rockville Pike\n<Rte. 240), Rockville, Md.\nHome guilders ter 25 Yeats\nL r\\ 1